text: Aqhuya Aqhuyani (Aymara aqhuya faint, dull, disfigured, see: Mortecino tear stained, (see: Tener ojos lagrimados) -ni a suffix to indicate ownership, also spelled Ako Akoani, Akoa Akoani)Bolivian IGM map 1:50,000 Lago Khara Kkota 5945-IV is a peak in the Cordillera Real in the Andes of Bolivia. It is situated in the La Paz Department, Larecaja Province, Guanay Municipality. Aqhuya Aqhuyani lies northeast of Mullu Apachita and northwest of the village of Uma Pallqa (Uma Palca) and Turini.
